# Work scopes — keep them separate

This repo has three parallel tracks. Do not merge them in one change unless the owner asks.

## 1. Legacy Designer documentation (owner-led)

- **Goal**: Accurate specs in `Tawala_Key_Documents/DESIGNER_*.md` from screenshots and owner notes.
- **Output**: Markdown specs + gap tables vs `designer-web`.
- **Not required**: Implementing features in code the same session.

## 2. Browser Designer (`designer-web/`)

- **Goal**: Reimplement legacy Designer behavior in the browser.
- **Source of truth**: `Tawala_Key_Documents/DESIGNER_*.md` + `TawalaDesigner/` C# code.
- **Preview/deploy**: Local 5173/3001 and optionally 8080 — never www.tawala.com by default.

## 3. Registration / DirtBowl runtime parity (8080)

- **Goal**: End-user forms on Tomcat match expected layout and behavior (e.g. DirtBowl Registration).
- **Typical paths**: `designer-web/server/registrationFibToXml.mjs`, `docker/tomcat/css/`, deploy scripts.
- **Paused items** (unless owner reopens): Page 2+, Review headers, RegStep2, full theme parity across all pages.

## Default priorities when unclear

1. Owner is documenting UI → update specs, do not refactor code.
2. Owner asks to implement a Designer feature → `designer-web/` + cite spec section.
3. Owner asks about Registration look/feel on 8080 → runtime XML/CSS/deploy, not palette UX.

## Commits and PRs

Only commit or open PRs when the owner explicitly asks. Documentation-only sessions usually need no git activity.
